2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new neural language model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural language model. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms, but it may still be relevant as the paper deals with handling large vocabularies and out of vocabulary words.
